To write a unit test for the `initLinkSub()` and `scrollToAnchor()` functions, we'll use a testing framework like Jasmine along with Angular's TestBed. Below is a sample test suite that covers these functions. Please ensure to adjust the imports at the beginning of the test to match your project structure.

```typescript
import { ComponentFixture, TestBed } from '@angular/core/testing';
import { ErrorHandlerService } from 'path/to/your/error-handler.service';
import { YourComponent } from 'path/to/your/your.component';
import { ActivatedRoute } from '@angular/router';
import { GetTuneMyMusicTokenGQL } from 'path/to/your/get-tune-my-music-token-gql.service';
import { of } from 'rxjs';

describe('YourComponent', () => {
  let component: YourComponent;
  let fixture: ComponentFixture<YourComponent>;
  let errorHandlerService: ErrorHandlerService;
  let getTuneMyMusicTokenGQL: GetTuneMyMusicTokenGQL;
  let activatedRoute: ActivatedRoute;

  beforeEach(async () => {
    await TestBed.configureTestingModule({
      declarations: [YourComponent],
      providers: [
        { provide: ErrorHandlerService, useValue: jasmine.createSpyObj('ErrorHandlerService', ['catchErrorInPipeWithNullResult']) },
        { provide: GetTuneMyMusicTokenGQL, useValue: jasmine.createSpyObj('GetTuneMyMusicTokenGQL', ['fetch']) },
        { provide: ActivatedRoute, useValue: { snapshot: { fragment: null } } },
      ],
    }).compileComponents();
  });

  beforeEach(() => {
    fixture = TestBed.createComponent(YourComponent);
    component = fixture.componentInstance;
    errorHandlerService = TestBed.inject(ErrorHandlerService);
    getTuneMyMusicTokenGQL = TestBed.inject(GetTuneMyMusicTokenGQL);
    activatedRoute = TestBed.inject(ActivatedRoute);

    fixture.detectChanges();
  });

  afterEach(() => {
    fixture.destroy();
  });

  it('should initialize link subscription correctly', () => {
    const queryResult = {
      data: {
        getTuneMyMusicToken: {
          tmmUrl: 'https://example.com/token_url',
        },
      },
    };

    getTuneMyMusicTokenGQL.fetch.and.returnValue(of(queryResult));
    errorHandlerService.catchErrorInPipeWithNullResult.and.callFake((arg) => arg);

    component.initLinkSub();

    expect(component.TMMLink).toEqual(queryResult.data.getTuneMyMusicToken.tmmUrl);
  });

  it('should scroll to anchor if fragment exists', () => {
    activatedRoute.snapshot.fragment = 'tmm';

    const scrollToSpy = spyOn(component.tmm.nativeElement, 'scrollIntoView');

    component.scrollToAnchor();

    expect(scrollToSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith({ behavior: 'smooth' });
  });

  it('should not scroll to anchor if fragment is empty', () => {
    activatedRoute.snapshot.fragment = '';

    const scrollToSpy = spyOn(component.tmm.nativeElement, 'scrollIntoView');

    component.scrollToAnchor();

    expect(scrollToSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });
});
```

This test suite checks the following:

1. If `initLinkSub()` initializes the link subscription correctly.
2. If `scrollToAnchor()` scrolls to the anchor element when a fragment is present.
3. If `scrollToAnchor()` does not scroll to the anchor element when a fragment is absent.

