To calculate the median and mode of a given dataset in Go code, you can use the "math" package to sort the dataset using the "sort.Sort" function and then use the "math.Min" and "math.Max" functions to calculate the median and mode respectively.

Here is an example code snippet to calculate both the median and mode of a dataset stored in a slice of integers called "data":

```
import "sort"

func medianAndMode(data []int) (float64, float64) {
    sort.Ints(data)
    length := len(data)
    if length % 2 == 1 {
        return float64(data[length/2]), float64(data[length/2])
    }
    mid := float64(data[length/2 - 1])
    left_half := sort.Search(data[:length/2], func(i int) bool {
        return mid < float64(data[i])
    })
    right_half := sort.Search(data[left_half:], func(i int) bool {
        return mid < float64(data[i])
    })
    mid = float64(data[left_half])
    return mid, float64(data[right_half])
}
```

Regarding the differences between mean, median, and mode, they are all measures of central tendency, but they differ in their calculation methods and how they respond to outliers.

- The mean is the average of the dataset, and it is calculated by adding all the values and dividing by the number of values. This measure is highly sensitive to outliers, i.e., values that are far from the typical value in the dataset.
- The median is the middle value of the dataset when it is sorted in order. It is a robust measure, meaning it is not affected by outliers. It is usually calculated using either sorting the dataset and counting from the sorted list or using an existing algorithm like the Powell method.
- The mode is the most frequent value in the dataset. This measure is useful in categorical data analysis, where the data is categorized into a few discrete values. Unlike the mean and median, it cannot be easily computed for continuous data.

Regarding SQL queries for calculating these measures, here are some sample queries:

To calculate the mean:
```
SELECT AVG(column_name) FROM table_name;
```
To calculate the median:
```
SELECT MEDIAN(column_name) FROM table_name;
```
To calculate the mode:
```
SELECT MOST_FREQUENT_VALUE(column_name) FROM table_name;
```

Note that the above queries may require some additional configuration or extensions depending on your database platform.

