An image can be selected in a file input in several ways. If you're using a standard HTML file input, images are typically selected through the "Drag and Drop" or "Click to select" method.

If you want to display the selected images in a specific order when the file input is submitted, you can try the following method:

1. First, make sure your file input accepts multiple files, usually indicated by the "multiple" attribute in the input tag, like this:
```html
<input type="file" accept="image/*" multiple>
```
This will allow the user to select multiple images.

1. Then, you can use the "target" attribute to specify a name for the image files, which can be helpful for keeping track of the order. For example:
```html
<input type="file" accept="image/*" multiple name="images" id="images">
<script>
    const imagesInput = document.getElementById('images'); // retrieve the element in JavaScript
    imagesInput.addEventListener('change', (event) => { // listen for file changes
        const files = event.target.files; // get the selected files

        // Generate file name based on the timestamp when the file was selected
        const timestamp = new Date().toISOString().replace(/[^\d]/g, '');

        Array.from(files).forEach((file) => {
            const targetValue = `image${timestamp}&${file.name}`;
            imagesInput.target.value += `${targetValue}\n`;
        });
    });
</script>
```
This code sets the `name` attribute of the file input to `images` and creates a JavaScript function that is triggered when the user selects or drags files into the input. It then creates a target value by appending the file name with a timestamp, a separator, and the original file name. This target value will be used to keep track of the order of the images. When the file input changes, it updates the input's value with the target value, separated by a newline, effectively preserving the order of the images.

By following these steps, you should be able to maintain the order of the selected images accurately, as long as the images are selected through the file input and the naming convention is followed consistently.

